section.text:

          Title XXVIII of the Public Health Service Act (
          42 U.S.C. 300hh et seq.
        ) is amended by adding at the
			 end the following:

paragraph.text:
complete the
			 development of such strategy not later than 18 months after the date of
			 enactment of this Act;

implement such strategy, to the extent
			 practicable, not later than 3 years after the date of enactment of the Field EMS Innovation Act;
			 and

to promote
			 excellence in all aspects of the provision of field EMS by field EMS
			 agencies;

to promote
			 universal access to and availability of high-quality field EMS in all
			 geographic locations of the Nation;

to sustain field EMS practitioners to ensure
			 24 hours a day, 7 days a week readiness and preparedness at the local
			 level;

to improve
			 coordination between regional field EMS systems and integration of such
			 regional field EMS systems into the larger health care system;

subparagraph.text:
trauma (in a
			 manner that is complementary and not duplicative of other trauma data
			 collection, such as the National Trauma Data Bank);

paragraph.text:
to implement and
			 evaluate system-wide quality improvement initiatives, including medical
			 direction at the State, local, and regional levels;

subparagraph.text:
the recommendations of the Assistant Secretary for
			 Preparedness
			 and Response, FICEMS, NEMSAC, and relevant stakeholders;

the needs and resource limitations of volunteer, smaller agencies, and
			 agencies
			 in rural areas;

paragraph.text:
evaluate education and training courses and
			 methodologies to identify optimal educational modalities for field EMS
			 practitioners;

enhance the
			 opportunity for medical direction training and for promoting appropriate
			 medical oversight of field emergency medical care;

clause.text:
when medically
			 necessary, the evaluation, treatment, or referral of patients to other
			 medically appropriate health care providers;

subparagraph.text:
